import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    group_counts = data['group'].value_counts()
    ax = sns.barplot(x=group_counts.index, y=group_counts.values)
    ax.set(xlabel='Group', ylabel='Count')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of groups in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    group_counts = data['group'].value_counts()
    plt.pie(group_counts, labels=group_counts.index, autopct='%.1f%%')
    plt.title('What is the most common group in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(group_counts.index, title="Groups", loc="upper right")
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data_counts = data.groupby(['group', 'person']).size().reset_index(name='counts')
    chart = sns.barplot(x='group', y='counts', hue='person', data=data_counts, ci=None)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of people across the groups?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(title='Person', loc='upper right')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data_group_count = data.groupby('group').count().reset_index()
    ax = sns.boxplot(x='group', y='person', data=data_group_count)
    plt.title('What is the average number of people per group?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Group')
    plt.ylabel('Person Count')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    unique_person_counts = data['person'].value_counts()
    sns.histplot(unique_person_counts, bins=range(1, unique_person_counts.max() + 1), kde=False, color='blue')
    plt.xlabel('Unique Person Counts')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of unique people in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
